# The DCA exam & where next

**55 questions · 90 min · ~65–70% · valid 2 yrs.** Its six domains *are* this course:

| Domain | Wt | Modules |
|---|---|---|
| Orchestration | ~25% | 09 |
| Images & registry | ~20% | 02, 07 |
| Install & config | ~15% | 10 |
| Networking | ~15% | 05 |
| Security | ~15% | 08 |
| Storage | ~10% | 04 |

## Memorise vs look up · practise

**Memorise:** `run` flags · volume/bind/tmpfs · name DNS + routing mesh · `CMD`/`ENTRYPOINT`, `COPY`/`ADD` · services vs tasks · `deploy:` keys. **Look up:** rare `daemon.json` keys. **Practise** a real 3-node Swarm.

## Where next

**Kubernetes** — same images, richer model: **CKAD → CKA → CKS**. Or cloud (ECS/EKS, GKE, AKS).

You hold the whole model: **image → container → network → volume → registry → hardened → orchestrated.** Built one map at a time.
